# MeterVerse Toolchain Rules

## Tools
- **Playwright** — browser automation and testing (auto-run on UI changes)
- **SpecKit** — specification generation
- **Graphify** — knowledge graph generation
- **Dependency Cruiser** — dependency analysis (run on every change)
- **Madge** — circular dependency check (run on every change)
- **Lighthouse** — performance audit (run before deployment)
- **axe** — accessibility audit (run before deployment)
- **Semgrep** — SAST security scan (run on code changes)
- **Trivy** — container/filesystem vulnerability scan (run weekly)
- **Snyk** — dependency vulnerability scan (run on dependency changes)
- **Spectral** — API specification linting (run on API changes)

## Quality Gates
Every task must pass these gates:
1. `tsc --noEmit` — zero errors
2. `eslint . --ext .ts,.tsx` — zero errors
3. `depcruise src --output-type err` — no violations
4. `madge --circular src/index.ts` — no circular deps

## Failure Reporting
Failures are written to `D:\meter\reports\{tool}-{timestamp}.{format}` and summarized in the task output.
